# English UI copy capitalization (`en-US`)

- **Audience**: **`L_*.ts`** labels, markdown headings under **`i18n/en-US/documents/`** in dialogs, **`globalFunctionality`** beside actions, **`dialogs.keybindSettings.commands.*`**, **`quasarNotify`**, Storybook **`externalFileLoader`** strings aligned with shipped titles, Playwright asserts on **`$t`** text, **bold UI references** in **`documents/changeLog.md`** quoting shipped chrome.
- **Running prose**: Sentence-style — capitalize **first word** (each introductory segment for slash-linked heads e.g. **Import / Export**). Ordinary words afterward **lowercase** unless acronyms, brands, product tokens, or full **Fantasia Archive** (below).
- **Chrome labels / capital menu titles** — **headline-style**: principal words on top-bar **submenu** rows under **`AppControlMenus`**, matching **Splash** primary actions reusing menu wording, **Keybind Settings** command names (**`dialogs.keybindSettings.commands.*`**) + dialog header + matching primary-action labels, major **dialog** headings (e.g. **Fantasia Archive Settings**, **Import / Export App Configuration**), **`globalFunctionality.faActionManager.labels`** aligned with keyboard actions, checklist captions beside toggles in those flows, discrete **floating-window** headings (**Custom App CSS**, **App Noteboard**, etc.). **Short-word lowercasing** where conventional English headlines do (**the**, **to**, **into**, **a**, **an**, **and**, **but**, **or**, **nor**, **as**, **at**, **by**, **for**, **from**, **in**, **of**, **off**, **on**, **onto**, **out**, **over**, **with** when medial not phrase-leading). Prefer exact locale strings over mechanical title-casing.
- **Top chrome menu `title` strings**: **`L_project`**, **`L_documents`**, **`L_tools`**, **`L_helpInfo`** (e.g. **Project**, **Content**, **App controls**, **Help**) — deliberate title casing independent of submenu rules; submenu rows follow headline pattern above.
- **Compound rows**: e.g. **Tips, Tricks & Trivia** — commas + **`&`** with headline intent; **`&`** stays capitalized per locale — do not downgrade **&**-linked segments for sentence prose.
- **Canonical markdown headings** in dialogs: **Advanced Search Guide**, **Tips, Tricks & Trivia** — match **`i18n/en-US/documents/*.md`** H1 casing.
- **Keep literal casing** for tokens: **`CSS`**, **`FA`**, **`HTML`**, **`JSON`**, **`UUID`**, **`IPC`**, **`OS`**, **`UI`**, **`FA 1.0`**, **`F1`**, **`Electron`**, **`Monaco`**, **`Quasar`**, **`SQLite`**, **`Storybook`**, **`TypeScript`**, **`Vite`**, **`Vue`**, **`macOS`**, **`Markdown`**, **Fantasia Archive**, **About Fantasia Archive**, platforms/brands (**Discord**, **GitHub**, **Grammarly**, **Ko-Fi**, **Patreon**, **Reddit**, **WebM**, **Windows**, **Linux**). User demos may shout **`YOUR KEY`** when illustrative.
- **Other locales**: Do not impose English headline rules on **German** (capitalized nouns) or **French**; mirror **roles** per target-language norms (**de**, **fr** menus refreshed alongside **noteboard** terminology).

